included.description:
The Microelectronics Research Center located in west Ames is a multidisciplinary center focusing on the study of semiconductor materials, devices, and applications. The diffusion furnaces located there are used as part of the EE 432/532 courses titled "Microelectronics Fabrication Techniques". The students and professors of these courses perform laboratory exercises to fabricate electronic chip wafers. The need for an accurate temperature controller is essential in the fabrication process. The previous temperature controllers were out-dated analog controllers that were no longer precise enough for the new generation of electronic chip wafers.The Diffusion Furnace Temperature Controller Design is an upgrading of the previous temperature controller system. The design is completed a new set of temperature controllers will be integrated into the diffusion furnaces located at the Microelectronics Research Center. An extension of the design is to provide a softwareinterface, so that the temperature of the furnaces can be controlled and monitored remotely. 
All the innovation and design principles that have been produced have been independent with the support of our client/advisor.The new digital temperature controller (CN616) is installed in the same place where the previous controllers were, in the furnace at the Microelectronics Research Center. The controllers will be used in an environmentally controlled lab, and thus will not have any environmental issues.
included.title: Remote Control Diffusion Furnace Controller

included.description:
Home control system applications on mobile platform specially design for senior citizens. Too many features for them might be a nightmare and keep them away of using the home control system. So features should be limited to what they will need the most in their daily life. Based on one research paper, communication is one of most wanted feature by senior citizens. Like Skype, they would like this kind of app to voice chat or video chat with their family members who are not living closely and some other friends. Other features like light controls and AC controls are commonly used in their life. And most of them will forget things like taking medications, paying utility bills or an item in shopping list. So all these features will be the main features I am going to design for senior citizens.
Mi-Fi Prototyping Link: http://share.axure.com/ZS7V5X
included.title: Interaction Design: Home Control System for Senior Citizens (Mid-Fi Prototype)

included.description: The REACH (REmote ACcess to smart Home facility) platform is to allow students to learn about basic principles of computer science and software engineering practices, and gain hands-on experience through observable effects of the computing systems in a familiar setting (home). It utilizes virtualization to encourage group collaboration and grants anytime, anywhere access to the smart home facility. It incorporates dynamic binding capability that allows students to either use the sensors and actuators hardware they check out and install locally for development, or to conduct experiments in the smart home facility. Once the development is completed, the programs can be deployed remotely, and students can make observations through web cams strategically situated in the smart home facility and the logs of the system's operations and users' activities. The REACH platform is designed to support a large spectrum of computer science courses, from the equivalence of computer science lab 101, interdisciplinary projects, all the way to research projects in artificial intelligence, pervasive computing, and human computer interactions.
included.title: Virtualization in Smart Home Lab

included.description: In our daily lives, it is always hard to receive or send a message at the right time. For example, you try to remind your best friend John to pick up a textbook before he leaves the library. It is difficult to know when he might leave the library. If you send the message to early, is he going to remember that he has to pick up the book before leaving library? Another example is you are going to school in a snow day. You want to catch the bus right on time without standing outside freezing. If you miss the bus, you are going to end up waiting longer. How could you know the bus is coming on time or not? For the situations described above, we decide to create a location-based message system. It can send or receive a message based on location trigger. For example, you set the condition that when John move out of the library area, he will receive the message that reminds him to get the textbook from you. When the bus enters one-block-range of the bus stop, the system will send you a message that reminds you to get ready

included.description: The College of Pharmacy is the University of Michigan's center of education for future pharmacists and pharmaceutical scientists. The college is large and widespread, with a good amount of its students and faculty working in the community. There are many departments, who function fairly autonomously, that operate under a collection of deans and administrative directors. The college is currently undergoing overhauls to their central office space, as well as their website. A spirit of change and forward-looking perspective has infected the organization, and their proposal reflects this attitude and a considerable amount of preliminary thought and investigation into their information needs. Our group was asked to study the flow of information policy and procedure, which several people maintain from different departments of the college. There are many formats for sharing and storage, and a multitude of key documents involved in the problematic information flow. Users range from current employees and students to new, incoming employees and students who rely on the student and faculty handbooks for policy and guidance. The college is organized in a decentralized fashion both physically and virtually, and they lack an efficient intranet for communication and information exchange.
included.title: Contextual Inquiry: College of Pharmacy

included.name: Medbuddy: A Mobile Medicinal Management System for Children with ADD/ADHD
included.description: ADD/ADHD is a chronic, debilitating disorder that can cause patients to be forgetful and disorganized due to the lack of attention. It can be especially disruptive if the patient were a child. Although the exact regimen prescribed is adjusted on a case-to-case basis, the most effective treatment often involves a combination of medicines and behavioral therapies. Medbuddy is a mobile medication management system designed to improve young patients' compliance to the prescription instructions, while attempting to affect positive changes in their behaviors by establishing structured and consistent daily routines and providing both positive and negative feedbacks. By providing timely reminders when it's time to take medications, establishing a reward schedule to reinforce positive behaviors, and interacting with child patients with a configurable avatar, Medbuddy is designed to be an agent of fun that combines medicinal and behavioral treatments to make ADD/ADHD child patients better so they may develop their full potentials.
